    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A P0171 code, indicating running lean, could be a sign of a few different issues. Since you've checked the MAF sensor and it's fine, you might want to check the fuel injectors, as they can sometimes be the culprits in a lean-running scenario. It's also worth checking the O2 sensors, as they can affect the air-fuel mixture. If those don't seem to be the problem, you might want to look at the fuel pump or fuel pressure regulator. If you're still having trouble, a professional mechanic might be able to help you diagnose the issue. Good luck!",
      "source": "target",
